Step 2-a. Calculating Design Power
(MXL / XL / L / H / S_M / MTS_M / T Series)
Design Power (Pd) =Transmission Power (Pt) x Overload Factor (Ks)
– Calculate Transmission Power at Motor Rated Power Output. (Ideally should be calculated with the load applied to the belt)
– Overload Factor (Ks)=Ko+Kr+Ki (Ko: Overload Correction Factor (Table 1) Kr: Rotation Ratio Correction Factor (Table 2) Ki: Idler Correction Factor (Table 3)
Step 2-b. Calculating Design Power
(For P_M/UP_M Series)
Design Power (Pd) =Transmission Power (Pt) x Overload Factor (Ks)
– Calculate Transmission Power at Motor Rated Power Output. (Ideally should be calculated with the load applied to the belt)
– Normal Motor Load Factor (Ks)=Ko+Ki+Kr+Kh
Ko: Application Coefcient (Table 4) Ki: Idler Correction Factor (Table 5) Kr: Speed Multiplication Correction Factor (Table 6) Kh: Operation Time Correction Factor (Table 7)
